modules.description: Provides serialization of rule data structures into S-expressions using a custom conversion function. Operates on a type representing parsing or transformation rules, enabling structured output for debugging or logging. Used to generate human-readable representations during compiler or parser diagnostics.

Provides functions for asynchronous file I/O, process execution, and time manipulation tailored for expect tests. Works with async threads, process handles, and file paths. Used to verify command output, manage temporary files, and control execution timing in test scenarios.

Serializes rule data structures into S-expressions using custom conversion functions, allowing structured debugging output. It operates on a type representing parsing or transformation rules, enabling detailed inspection during compiler diagnostics. Users can generate human-readable representations of rule states for analysis or logging. This supports tasks like tracing rule application or validating transformation logic in async workflows.
